  "description": [
    "Atomic Age Began Year Ago This Week Editors NoteThe following story and others by Paul Harrison are designed for use in connection with the first an Hirers ary of the atom bombings of Hiroshima Aug 6 and Nagasaki Aug 9 BY PAUL HARRISON United Press Staff Correspondent Washington Aug 8UPThe atomic age is one year old this month In scientific terminology it is really the nuclear age In an historic moment a year ago science harnessed the core of the atomthe atomic nucleus It was the release of nuclear energy from the worlds first fis sion bomb that created the fleet ing crashing noonday in the dark ness of a vast expanse of New Mex ican desert on July 16 1945 The atomic age was born in newspaper headlines and in the throats of radio announcers less than a month later when the world learned of the astounding fact that one bomb had obliterated an entire city in Japan and that another a few days later nearly wiped out a second city The Atom Was Magic For years there had been fairy tale talk of harnessing the atom Atomic caught the public imagi nation Now even scientists curb their bent"
  ],
